Aer V. SCENE I. Thais attacks Pythias about Dorus. What is the meaning of all this prevarication? Here is Pamphila in the utmost distress and disorder; and the eunuch is gone off. Pythias explains what she has heard from Dorus, that it was Chaerea who had been introduced into their house, and who had been left alone with Pamphila by Thais’ own orders. At this moment they see Chaerea approaching, still in the clothes of Dorus, which he has not yet had an opportunity of getting rid of.
